The first argument after "read -c" seems to be skipped, e.g.

$ repl () {
        read -c a0 a1 a2 a3
        echo
        echo "a0:" $a0
        echo "a1:" $a1
        echo "a2:" $a2
        echo "a3:" $a3
        reply=()
}
$ compctl -K repl testrepl
$ testrepl x y z [TAB]   (note: AUTO_MENU and LIST_AMBIGUOUS are set)
a0:
a1: testrepl
a2: x
a3: y

a0:
a1: testrepl
a2: x
a3: y

instead of

a0: testrepl
a1: x
a2: y
a3: z
...

